INSERT INTO Intellibot.TrainingData(question,answer) VALUES("In class when we discussed polynomial regression for a 1D variable, I believe it was mentioned that the training error should be decreasing as the order P of the polynomial increases, since a higher-order polynomial can mimic any lower-order polynomial by setting higher weights = 0. However when I run polyreg.m, using the entire data set of problem1.mat as training data, as the orders increase, there are some cases when a higher order run has larger training error than a lower order run, which is contrary to what was said in lecture. Is this something that occurs in practice for high enough orders?", "What you saw in class is true.You should look more closely to the range of values of your data, and keep in mind that numerical inconsistencies might appear. ");
