INSERT INTO Intellibot.TrainingData(question,answer) VALUES("So I think I have gradient descent working - my algorithm seems to behave as it should. However, I get a different theta each time. I know one of the slides said that the R(theta) is convex so gradient descent always converges to the same solution, but I haven't been able to get that to happen. Is there any reason why I might be seeing this? Could I have possibly calculated the gradient incorrectly?","When you are pretty close to the solution, with a large step size you can find yourself 'stepping over' the optimal solution, in that case you might see an increase in the loss function. You can fix that by either reducing the step size so that you can get closer to the solution or reducing the tolerance so that the last step is not taken to begin with.");
