INSERT INTO Intellibot.TrainingData(question,answer) VALUES("If I made a modification to polyreg.m (eg. removed the plotting code) but left everything else pretty much alone, should I include it in my submission?","It's ok to re-upload the slightly modified polyreg.m. We just don't want folks to upload tons of standard functions (like Steve Gunn's entire codebase) and to upload massive datasets onto Courseworks because it takes up bandwidth and storage.");
INSERT INTO Intellibot.TrainingData(question,answer) VALUES("I'm having trouble understanding the terminology in problem 1C.  Is each function in C one of c0...c10 so e.g. c1(100) = 1, c1(200) = -1? Thanks!","There are a lot of confusions due to this question.Think of it this way:Alice chooses d points between 1 and 999.Bob attributes a label to each of these points.Alice look into here set of classifiers c0, ..., c9. If the first point is 15 then c1 classifies it as +1, c5 as +1, c2 as -1 etc. If she can classifies the d points as Bob asked, she wins, otherwise Bob wins. If Alice can find d points so that Bob cannot win, it means that the VC dimension is at least d.To prove that the VC dimension of C is inferior to d, you need to prove that whatever d points Alice choses, Bob can always find a ways to win. If it does not help, please come at my OH.");
