INSERT INTO Intellibot.TrainingData(question,answer) VALUES("about SVM: Hi, I don't understand why the sum of the \alpha_i in the dual formulation of the sum  is equal to 1 (topic 6 slide 6, first time we see \alpha) according to the TA. And if so, why bother putting it in the expression to optimise?","I think you may have misunderstood my statements during OH. It's not that ?iai=1. In the linearly separable case that we were discussing, we have ?ji=0ai=?ni=j+1ai=1, where j splits the two classes.This is why we can say ?iaiYi=0, and is derived from the fact that a comes from the coordinate transform to barycentric coordinates.");
