INSERT INTO Intellibot.TrainingData(question,answer) VALUES("Midterm sample question 2b Reposting another student's question from yesterday since we never got an answer...Can any one explain the answer of midterm sample question 2a ? Thanks !In addition, we never got a response to our request for an answer to 2b, which is missing from the answer key for the sample midterm. Anyone? Bueller? Bueller?","The order will matter. The margin will be different depending on the order.In the case where the kernel used is a linear kernel, e.g. k(xi,xj)=x?ixj, the kernelized algorithm should give the exact same results and updates as the non-kernelized algorithm. Do not derive gradient descent with the kernelized version, just look at how to implement the standard non-kernelized update rule where you store N alphas instead of D w values. The kernelized algorithm is just a different way of storing the model (and a different way of implementing the update rule and the prediction rule). In the linear case, both schemes (oriinal and kernelized) should be consistent (they produce the same mistakes and the same predictions).");
