INSERT INTO Intellibot.TrainingData(question,answer) VALUES("HW3 Problem 5 After it finishes gradient descent with Test data, I ran the prediction with Training data. However, out of 1000 prediction there are about 450 wrong decisions. The error rate seems to high. Is it normal?","Check your functions again, I had this problem since I mistakenly calculated norm to compute kernels (I took square root) After fixing this I got about 10% error. Also, step size is very important, monitor norm of gradient at each iteration to find a good and reasonable interval for step size.");
INSERT INTO Intellibot.TrainingData(question,answer) VALUES("HW3 Q2 clarification I want to make sure that µML means the maximum likelihood estimation given the data and not considering the prior distribution correct?  And µMAP means the maximum likelihood estimation taking into account the prior and the data?Also P(H | D) means evaluating P(H) using P(µ|D) correct?","Yes, Yes and Yes.");
INSERT INTO Intellibot.TrainingData(question,answer) VALUES("Looking up solutions online.I was just wondering if the academic honesty policy is strictly enforced. I often struggle with questions and am forced to submit partial solution or submit late. At the same time, I know of some students who just copy the answers posted online to the questions getting full marks in home-work.","Academic honesty policy is always strictly enforced. If you know of students who are cheating in any way, please let us know so that we can investigate.For those of you who may have considered doing things like this: the homework is intended to exercise your understanding of concepts and techniques learned in class. Cheating on the homework -- even if you never get caught -- is only cheating yourself of learning, which will show on quizzes and exams.If you are stuck on the homework, please come to office hours and/or post your questions to Piazza. Also, it's probably in your best interest to start as early as possible.");
